<HEADLINE>
WHO hails China's single-dose swine flu vaccine
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Geneva, Sept 3, 2009 (AFP)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The World Health Organisation on Thursday hailed China's first home-grown swine
flu vaccine and congratulated pharmaceutical firm Sinovac for its "rapid" work.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese were very rapid on this, and we can congratulate them for having
shared their trial results with us," said Marie-Paule Kieny, who heads the UN
health agency's vaccine research.
</P>
</TEXT>
